article_title: Private Insurance Exchanges Thrive While Obamacare's Falter

article_metadata.author: Sally Pipes

og.description: While Obamacare's health insurance exchanges stumble, private exchanges are thriving. They offer companies and patients access to high-quality care at reduced cost. Yet these private exchanges -- like so much else that’s actually working in the private healthcare market -- are at risk because of the heavy government hand of Obamacare.
